    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-black mb-1">Accessibility Statement</h1>
    <p class="text-ink/50 text-sm">Effective date: 21 June 2026 · Applies to thaiholidaybudget.com</p>

    <p>Genext Information Systems is committed to making thaiholidaybudget.com usable by as many people as possible, including people who rely on assistive technology. Accessibility is an ongoing effort, and we welcome feedback that helps us improve.</p>

    <h2>1. Conformance target</h2>
    <p>We aim to align with the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 at Level AA. While we cannot guarantee full conformance at all times, these guidelines shape how we build and maintain the Service. This statement reflects our current status and is reviewed periodically.</p>

    <h2>2. Measures we take</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Responsive, mobile-first layout</strong> that adapts from small phones to large screens and supports browser zoom and text resizing.</li>
      <li><strong>Semantic HTML</strong> with labelled form controls, so screen readers can announce each field.</li>
      <li><strong>Keyboard operability</strong> for the step navigation, buttons, sliders, and links.</li>
      <li><strong>Light and dark themes</strong> with a one-tap toggle; both use high-contrast text, and key totals are presented as text, not images.</li>
      <li><strong>No flashing or strobing content</strong> that could trigger photosensitive reactions.</li>
      <li><strong>Plain-language guidance</strong> at each step, with figures shown in both your chosen currency and Thai baht.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Known limitations</h2>
    <p>We are transparent about areas we are still improving:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Range sliders are easiest with a pointer; we provide numeric fields and labels alongside them and continue to refine keyboard fine-control.</li>
      <li>Some emoji icons are decorative and may be announced by screen readers; we are improving their labelling.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Tips for a better experience</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Use your browser's zoom (Ctrl/Cmd and +) to enlarge text; the layout reflows cleanly.</li>
      <li>Prefer a brighter or dimmer page? Use the theme toggle in the header to switch between light and dark modes — your choice is remembered on your device.</li>
      <li>Every slider has a matching number you can read, and most selections can be overridden with direct numeric entry.</li>
      <li>Your progress is saved on your device, so you can take breaks without losing work.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Feedback and contact</h2>
    <p>If you encounter an accessibility barrier, we would like to know so we can address it. Please contact <a href="mailto:support@thaiholidaybudget.com">support@thaiholidaybudget.com</a>, describing the page, what you were trying to do, and the assistive technology you use. We aim to respond within a reasonable timeframe.</p>

    <h2>6. Updates</h2>
    <p>We review this statement periodically and update the effective date above when we make accessibility improvements.</p>
  </div>


